  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Helping NPO support centers in disaster relief</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Historic rainstorms caused floods and landslides in western Japan. Damages in Okayama and Hiroshima are particularly severe. With a network with local nonprofit organization (NPO) support centers across Japan, Japan NPO Center has been coordinating staff dispatch to the support centers in affected communities to help out the necessary operations. Your support compensates the staff&apos;s transportation to and accommodation in Hiroshima &amp; Okayama which are currently done with out of pocket expenses.</narrative>
  </description>
